The lecture course gives an overview of the major topics of general chemistry: the fundamentals of thermodynamics, chemical kinetics and equilibrium, properties of solutions, redox processes, the structure of matter.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give students the basic knowledge of chemistry necessary for further studying.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student having passed the course,  1.knows the concepts and principles of chemical thermodynamics and kinetics.   2.knows the methods of expressing of solution concentration and the general properties of solutions. 3.knows the processes in electrolyte solutions and is able to characterise them.  4.knows the principles of redox processes.  5.knows the fundamentals of atomic structure and chemical bonding.
